# Working with VIPS code tables
# -----------------------------
# Use a tool like jq to parse and list code table entries. For example:
# 1. List tables
# curl --silent --request GET --silent --user "user:${PASSWORD}"  https://digitalforms-viirp-api-c220ad-dev.apps.silver.devops.gov.bc.ca/digitalforms-viirp/v1/codetables/steve-test-9b022161-38ed-4688-92a8-12308128cd3f | jq '.configuration | keys'
#
# 2. Show individual table values
# curl --silent --request GET --silent --user "user:${PASSWORD}"  https://digitalforms-viirp-api-c220ad-dev.apps.silver.devops.gov.bc.ca/digitalforms-viirp/v1/codetables/steve-test-9b022161-38ed-4688-92a8-12308128cd3f | jq '.configuration | .addresses'
#
# 3. List sub-element matching codes
# - curl --silent --request GET --silent --user "user:${PASSWORD}"  https://digitalforms-viirp-api-c220ad-dev.apps.silver.devops.gov.bc.ca/digitalforms-viirp/v1/codetables/steve-test-9b022161-38ed-4688-92a8-12308128cd3f | jq '.configuration | .originalCauses[] | select(.noticeTypeCd=="IMP")'
#
# 4. List values for a table
# curl --silent --request GET --silent --user "user:${PASSWORD}"  https://digitalforms-viirp-api-c220ad-dev.apps.silver.devops.gov.bc.ca/digitalforms-viirp/v1/codetables/steve-test-9b022161-38ed-4688-92a8-12308128cd3f | jq -r '.configuration | .addresses[] | .objectCd'

### Code tables
GET https://{{host}}{{api_path}}/codetables/steve-test-{{$guid}}
Authorization: Basic {{api_username}} {{api_password}}
Accept: application/json


